ng!\r\n<!--more-->\r\nHah this is more!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2012-03-11 00:39:06','2012-03-11 00:39:06','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2012-03-04 02:32:17','2012-03-04 02:32:17','Great design is all around us, but no matter how many times we admire or take pleasure in a well-designed product, we rarely stop to consider the history and motivation behind it. Recognising this fact, at the end of 2011 Australia-born Asher Compton set about creating a website that would offer insight into the loves, lives and labours of some of the world’s most talented designers – and so Industry and Interest was born. Each month, Asher, who now lives in Canada, chats to Industry Leaders about their inspirations and aspirations,\r\nusing his signature laid-back interview style to reveal what really makes them tick.','About','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2012-04-06 15:43:15','2012-04-06 22:43:15','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(234,2,'2012-04-01 17:00:49','2012-04-02 00:00:49','','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-27','','','2012-04-01 17:00:49','2012-04-02 00:00:49','',2,'http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/2-revision-27/',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2012-03-04 16:46:03','2012-03-04 16:46:03','Asher Compton is a passionate designer originally from Sydney Australia, now residing in Canada. Industry and interest was launched by Asher at the end of 2011 with the goal to keep people informed as to what’s happening in the industry and who’s leading it.\r\n\r\nI&amp;I features regular interviews and posts on Design, Fashion, Super Cars, Photography, Architecture and more.','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-6','','','2012-03-04 16:46:03','2012-03-04 16:46:03','',2,'http://spiraldesign.ca/2-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2012-03-04 16:56:48','2012-03-04 16:56:48','','About Custom Fields','','inherit','open','open','','acf_about-custom-fields-3','','','2012-03-04 16:56:48','2012-03-04 16:56:48','',80,'http://spiraldesign.ca/acf_about-custom-fields-3/',0,'revision','',0),(4,1,'2012-03-04 03:02:55','2012-03-04 03:02:55','','Things of Interest','','publish','open','open','','posts','','','2012-03-25 22:07:39','2012-03-26 05:07:39','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?page_id=4',0,'page','',0),(5,1,'2012-03-04 03:02:49','2012-03-04 03:02:49','','Posts','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision','','','2012-03-04 03:02:49','2012-03-04 03:02:49','',4,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?p=5',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2012-03-21 03:06:57','2012-03-21 10:06:57','Verlander picked up where he left off, pitching two scoreless innings in his exhibition debut as the Detroit Tigers beat the Toronto Blue Jays 4-2 Monday. Verlander gave up one hit, struck out one and faced six batters, and said he felt ready for another inning. He went 24-5 last season, including a no-hitter at Toronto.<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAsked if he was watching his line or merely trying to get ready for April, Verlander had an immediate answer. \"One hit, no walks,\" he said. \"I keep score no matter what.\" It\'s that kind of intensity, along with a dazzling array of pitches, that made Verlander so dominant for the AL Central champions. Be it March or October, he\'s ready. \"I have a lot to work on this spring,\" he said. \"I need to get more control and I wasn\'t throwing my breaking ball for strikes, but it will come. I need to get a feel for my changeup, but that will also come.\"','ERLANDER TOSSES TWO SCORELESS','','trash','open','open','','im-a-post','','','2012-04-06 04:09:07','2012-04-06 11:09:07','',0,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?p=6',0,'post','',0),(7,1,'2012-03-04 03:06:55','2012-03-04 03:06:55','','I\'m a Post','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision','','','2012-03-04 03:06:55','2012-03-04 03:06:55','',6,'http://spiraldesign.ca/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,2,'2012-04-02 13:14:27','2012-04-02 20:14:27','Verlander picked up where he left off, pitching two scoreless 