culpture','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-6','','','2012-04-06 05:27:03','2012-04-06 12:27:03','',265,'http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/265-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(315,2,'2012-04-06 05:25:51','2012-04-06 12:25:51','Fashion photographer and filmmaker <a title=\"Jacob Sutton\" href=\"http://www.jacobsutton.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Jacob Sutton</a> swaps the studio for the slopes of Tignes in south-eastern France, with a luminous after hours short film starring Artec pro snowboarder <a title=\"william hughes\" href=\"http://www.artecsnowboards.com/team/wham-bam-am-crew/william-hughes\" target=\"_blank\">William Hughes</a>. This film sees Hughes light up the snow-covered French hills in a bespoke L.E.D. - enveloped suit.','LED Snowboarder','','inherit','open','open','','261-revision-5','','','2012-04-06 05:25:51','2012-04-06 12:25:51','',261,'http://iandi.spiraldesign.ca/261-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(316,2,'2012-04-06 05:27:33','2012-04-06 12:27:33','Shepard Fairey is an American street artist who emerged from the skateboarding and punk rock scene. He first became known for his André the Giant (<a title=\"obey\" href=\"http://obeygiant.com/\" target=\"_blank\">OBEY</a>) sticker campaign which is still going strong. He is also famous for creating a series of posters supporting Barack Obama’s 2008 candidacy for President of the United States, including the iconic “HOPE” portrait.<!--more--> In this interview Shepard talks about the influence graffiti, skateboarding and punk rock had on his life and the ways it has shaped his art career. Shepard also features in <a title=\"banksy\" href=\"http://www.banksy.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Banksy’s</a> Documentary - <a title=\"exit through the gift shop\" href=\"http://www.industryandinterest.com/post/15999883182/check-out-exit-through-the-gift-shop\" target=\"_self\">Exit through the gift shop</a>.','THE RISE','','inherit','open','open','','271-revision-6','','','2012-04-06 05:27:33','2012-04-06 12:27:33'